<div class="container-sm article-image w-full justify-center mt-4 mb-8">
<img class="w-full" alt="" src="https://i.pcmag.com/imagery/articles/04mAFYwr4fpRIlMBs6Fenfn-1.1597275884.fit_lim.jpg" srcset="https://i.pcmag.com/imagery/articles/04mAFYwr4fpRIlMBs6Fenfn-1.1597275884.fit_lim.size_400x250.jpg 400w, https://i.pcmag.com/imagery/articles/04mAFYwr4fpRIlMBs6Fenfn-1.1597275884.fit_lim.size_850x490.jpg 800w, https://i.pcmag.com/imagery/articles/04mAFYwr4fpRIlMBs6Fenfn-1.1597275884.fit_lim.size_1600x900.jpg 1600w" width="1961" height="1103" sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, (min-width: 850px) 850px">
</div>
<section class="container flex mb-8">
<div class="flex-shrink w-full 2xl:px-4">
<div class="flex flex-col xl:pr-6">
<article id="article" class="w-full rich-text" data-autopogo>
<center><small><em>(Credit: SNK)</em></small></center>
<br><p>The classic arcade cabinet, the Neo Geo Multi Video System, is getting a revival this fall.&nbsp;</p><p>On Wednesday, SNK introduced a successor to the machine called the <a href="http://www.snkmvsx.com/index.html" target="_blank">Neo Geo MVSX</a>. It&rsquo;ll come preinstalled with 50 Neo Geo titles, including games from the King of Fighters, Metal Slug, and Samurai Shodown series.&nbsp;</p><p>The product looks pretty similar to the <a href="https://www.pcmag.com/opinions/neo-geo-at-30-the-big-red-machines-legacy-lives-on">original cabinet</a>, which arrived 30 years ago and helped rejuvenate the arcade scene in the 1990s. However, SNK has upgraded the machine&rsquo;s display to support a 1,280-by-1,024-pixel resolution, an increase from the 320-by-224 resolution.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20768%20432'%3E%3Crect%20fill='%23f7f7f7'%20/%3E%3C/svg%3E" data-image-loader="https://i.pcmag.com/imagery/articles/04mAFYwr4fpRIlMBs6Fenfn-4.png" data-lazy-sized alt="The cabinet front view" data-image-path="articles/04mAFYwr4fpRIlMBs6Fenfn-4.png" class="my-4">
<div style="line-height:1.25 !important" class="-mt-4 mb-8">
<small>
</small>
</div>
<img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20768%20432'%3E%3Crect%20fill='%23f7f7f7'%20/%3E%3C/svg%3E" data-image-loader="https://i.pcmag.com/imagery/articles/04mAFYwr4fpRIlMBs6Fenfn-2.png" data-lazy-sized alt="The cabinet with the base stand." data-image-path="articles/04mAFYwr4fpRIlMBs6Fenfn-2.png" class="my-4">
<div style="line-height:1.25 !important" class="-mt-4 mb-8">
<small>
(Credit: SNK)
</small>
</div>
<p>Another perk is how the cabinet will let you pick a game, and decide whether to play the arcade version, or the Neo Geo home console version. In addition, SNK has included a &ldquo;scan line&rdquo; mode, which will replicate the lines the old CRT screens emitted when you played an arcade game.&nbsp;</p><p>The cabinet, which has a 17-inch LCD display, will also let you enjoy the games with a friend. The machine comes with two sets of joystick controls, each with six buttons.&nbsp;</p><div>
<div class="mx-0 md:ml-8 md:mr-24 py-4 border border-gray-light border-t border-b border-r-0 border-l-0">
<h3 class="font-bold font-brand text-lg uppercase mb-2">Recommended by Our Editors</h3>
<div class="flex flex-wrap">
<div class="inline-flex my-4 md:my-2 w-full">
