</a>
<div class="flex flex-col justify-center w-auto md:mr-20">
<a class="no-underline leading-tight inline-block align-middle" href="/news/segas-astro-city-mini-arcade-cabinet-will-include-36-games" data-module="related-recirc" data-item="related-recirc-list" data-element="related-recirc-link" data-position="3" x-track-ga-click>Sega's Astro City Mini Arcade Cabinet Will Include 36 Games</a>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20768%20432'%3E%3Crect%20fill='%23f7f7f7'%20/%3E%3C/svg%3E" data-image-loader="https://i.pcmag.com/imagery/articles/04mAFYwr4fpRIlMBs6Fenfn-3.png" data-lazy-sized alt="The controls on the cabinent" data-image-path="articles/04mAFYwr4fpRIlMBs6Fenfn-3.png" class="my-4">
<div style="line-height:1.25 !important" class="-mt-4 mb-8">
<small>
(Credit: SNK)
</small>
</div>
<p>For $449 you can buy the main game cabinet, which weighs in at 28 pounds. But pay another $50, and you&rsquo;ll get the 32-inch stand, which can prop it up like a normal arcade machine for a total height of close to 5 feet.&nbsp;</p><p>The website for the Neo Geo MVSX indicates the arcade cabinet will be released in October. However, the official Twitter <a href="https://twitter.com/MVSXHOMEARCADE/status/1293477306183426048" target="_blank">account</a> for the machine says pre-sales will begin in September while actual units will be delivered in November. You can check out the official Neo Geo MVSX <a href="http://www.snkmvsx.com/index.html" target="_blank">website</a> for the full list of games. </p><div>
<div class="relative w-full h-0" style="padding-bottom: 56.3%;" data-nosnippet="true">
